The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Wrestler seeks legal recourse
New Delhi: In a bid to take part in the trials for the selection of the wrestling team for the Olympic Games, freestyle grappler Kripa Shankar Patel on Friday sought legal recourse, claiming he would suffer irreparable loss and injury without a fair selection. In a petition filed on Friday, Patel charged the Wrestling Federation of India, ministry of sports, Indian Olympic Association and executive director of the Sports Authority of India with inaction, omission and negligence. (PTI)  Copyright 
